# OpenPanel — public clientId for analytics (visible in HTML by design).
# Provisioned at https://openpanel.dev → site settings.
# Used by src/components/Analytics.astro; gated on import.meta.env.PROD so
# localhost doesn't pollute the dashboard.
#
# For the GitHub Pages deploy, set this as a repo Variable (Settings →
# Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables) — .github/workflows/pages.yml
# injects it into the build via:
#   env: OPENPANEL_CLIENT_ID: ${{ vars.OPENPANEL_CLIENT_ID }}
#
# Also: the OpenPanel project's "supported domains" must include
# `https://lossless-group.github.io/` or browser events will be rejected
# with a 401 (the pattern that bit the other splash deploys — see
# context-v/prompts/Setup-Analytics-Across-Sites.md).
#
# This file is git-ignored when copied to .env. Never commit a populated .env.
OPENPANEL_CLIENT_ID=
